Today We Are Going To Play With HackTheBox Headless

Nmap scan

Port 22,5000 are open.

Homepage

It's a simple webpage.

/support

Let's test for xss.

/support

Payload didn't work, but we can check if this report page is vulnerable to xss attacks.

Xss in header

We can insert xss payload into a header.

Xss

First call is xss payload trigger on our web browser, 2nd is when admin checks the report.

Admin Cookie

From this payload we can steal admin cookie.

Admin Cookie

From above payload i was able to obtain is_admin cookie.

Ffuf

From ffuf directory fuzzing i was able to find 2 directories.

Dashboard

We don't have access.

Cookie

Adding is_admin cookie.

Dashboard as admin

Now we can access dashboard as admin after adding cookie, This page is generating reports based on user input.

Command injection

Most of times web tasks runs on system let's check for command injection.

Command injection

We can execute command as dvir user.

Command injection

Executing simple bash reverseshell.

Reverseshell as dvir (user)

Ippsec's favorite port worked again.

Sudo

We can execute command as any user.

/usr/bin/syscheck

This script checks if a process named initdb.sh is running using pgrep. If the process is not found, then it starts ./initdb.sh from the current folder, making it vulnerable to arbitrary code execution.

Arbitrary code execution

Created a bash script called initdb.sh and added the command we need to execute. In this case, I'm executing bash shell with -p flag.

Bash (root)

Bingo shell as root.
